An official letter from Caijing magazine.
《财经》杂志由中国证券市场研究中心主办，1998年创刊，秉承“独立、独家、独到”的新闻理念，以权威性、公正性、专业性报道见长，是政经学界决策者、研究者、管理者的必读刊物。
"Caijing" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was founded in 1998, upholding the news concept of "independence, exclusivity and originality," and providing authoritative, impartial and professional reports.
。
.
国内27省市区实现零新增，7省区和澳门现有病例清零。
China's 27 provinces and municipalities to achieve zero new cases, 7 provinces and Macao existing cases are zero.
美国进入紧急状态；欧洲多国封关自救文|《财经》数据研究员 徐进 图|《财经》视觉中心 编辑|郝洲一、国内输入病例首超本土新增图1今日国内简述：国内3月13日报告累计确诊病例80824例，武汉新增4例。
US emergency; Caijing data researcher Xu Jintu; Caijing Visual Center & # 160; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & nbsp;
武汉新增疑似首次为零。
Wuhan is suspected to be a new first time zero.
新增报告境外输入确诊病例7例（上海4例，甘肃2例，北京1例），海外输入病例首次超过本土新增。
Seven new confirmed cases were reported from overseas (4 in Shanghai, 2 in Gansu and 1 in Beijing), with overseas imports surpassing domestic imports for the first time.
27个省区市实现了零新增，有7个省市区和澳门特别行政区已实现在院病例归零。
Twenty-seven provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities have achieved zero additions, and seven provinces, municipalities and the Macao Special Administrative Region have achieved zero hospital admissions.
二、多国宣布国家紧急状态，疫情高峰还未到来图2海外新增病例突破1万。
Many countries have declared a state of emergency, the peak of the epidemic has not yet arrived Figure 2 Overseas new cases of more than 10, 000.
目前欧洲报告的新冠肺炎确诊和死亡病例超过中国以外其他国家和地区的总和。
Europe now reports more cases of diagnosis and death from pneumonia than countries and regions other than China combined.
图3欧洲已经成为新冠疫情的“震中”。
Figure 3 Europe has become the epicentre of the new crown epidemic.
世卫组织总干事谭德塞指出，目前欧洲每日的确诊数目比中国高峰期更多，全球（包含中国在内）死于疫情的人数突破5000，他形容这是一个“悲剧性的里程碑”。
The number of confirmed cases per day in Europe is now higher than the peak in China, with more than 5,000 deaths worldwide, including in China, he said, describing it as a "tragic milestone."
而世卫组织卫生紧急项目技术主管玛丽亚·范·科霍夫表示，现时无法估计疫情何时在全球到达高峰期。
But Maria van Kohoff, WHO's technical director of health emergency programs, said it was impossible to estimate when the epidemic would peak around the world.
三、美国进入紧急状态，特朗普本人将进行病毒检测图4美国似乎终于意识到了问题的严重性。
III. America in a state of emergency, Trump himself will be tested for the virus Figure 4 The United States finally seems to realize the seriousness of the problem.
当地时间3月13日下午，特朗普在白宫南草坪举行记者会，宣布美国进入应对新冠疫情紧急状态，联邦政府将启动500亿美元的紧急资金储备，用于各州医疗机构用于应对新冠肺炎疫情，同时要求各州尽快建立应对新冠肺炎的应急指挥中心。
On the afternoon of March 13, at a press conference on the South Lawn of the White House, Trump announced that the United States was entering a state of emergency in response to the New Crown Epidemic, and that the federal government would activate a $50 billion emergency reserve to be used by state health-care facilities to respond to the outbreak of pneumonia.
巴西总统的新闻秘书瓦恩加滕3月12日确诊感染新冠病毒，因此传出巴西总统博索纳罗也被感染的消息。
Brazilian President Jose Manuel Vincenzo Vincennes, press secretary to the President of Brazil, was diagnosed with the new crown virus on March 12, leading to word that Brazilian President Jose Manuel Bozonaro was also infected.
但是，博索纳罗13日进行病毒检测的结果呈阴性，他正在等待复检的结果。
However, Bosonaro 13 virus test results are negative, he is waiting for the results of re-examination.
瓦恩加滕3月初曾陪同博索纳罗访美，并曾与美国总统特朗普合照。
Wangateng accompanied Bozonaro to the United States in early March and took a group photo with US President Trump.
美国白宫多名政要曾在上周出席海湖庄园举行的晚宴，接待巴西代表团，亦曾在渡假村举行活动。
White House dignitaries attended a dinner at Lake Hills last week, hosted a Brazilian delegation and held events at the resort.
去过庄园的人当中已有4人确诊。
Four of the people who had been to the estate had been diagnosed.
因此，特朗普也非常担心被感染，他在13日的记者会上表示，“我非常有可能会进行新冠病毒检测。
So Trump is also very worried about getting infected, he told a news conference on the 13th. "I'm very likely to be tested for the new crown virus."
”图5美国正处于疫情爆发的初始阶段，新增病例已突破500，仅剩西弗吉尼亚州未报告感染病例，如不加快脚步、进行有效阻断，后果极其严重！按照特朗普的说法，美国将在3月底之前完成500万份新冠病毒检测，但实际执行情况仍有待观察。
Figure 5 The United States is in the early stages of an outbreak, with more than 500 new cases reported, except in West Virginia, with dire consequences if not accelerated and effectively halted! According to Trump, the US will have completed five million new crown jewels by the end of March, but actual implementation remains to be seen.
四、欧洲成为疫情“震中”，多国封关图6欧洲目前报告的病例数和死亡数已超过了除中国外世界上其他地区的总和。
Europe Becomes the epicentre of the epidemic, with more cases and deaths being reported in Europe than anywhere else in the world except China combined.
欧洲多国已加强封关和隔离措施。
Many European countries have strengthened closures and isolation measures.
西班牙单日新增确诊病例超过2000，首相桑切斯宣布该国进入紧急状态。
Prime Minister Sanchez declared a state of emergency in Spain, where more than 2,000 new cases were confirmed a day.
丹麦3月14日12时起全面封关，所有未能提出可信原因的外国人将不得入境。
Denmark imposed a complete closure at 1200 hours on 14 March, and all foreigners who failed to provide credible reasons would be denied entry.
这一措施将至少维持至4月13日。
This measure will be maintained at least until 13 April.
波兰当地时间3月15日凌晨0时起，除了政府派出接载国民的包机之外，将不会再有国际入境航班或火车。
There will be no more international inbound flights or trains except for charters sent by the Government to pick up nationals from 0 a.m. local time in Poland.
所有外国人不得入境，波兰公民回国也要接受14日隔离。
All foreigners are not allowed to enter the country and Polish citizens are segregated for 14 days upon their return.
捷克政府也已发出禁令，将自3月16日起禁止所有外籍人士入境，只有取得该国居留权或超过90天签证的人士可以入境，另外，捷克公民也将禁止出境。
The Czech Government had also issued a ban on the entry of all foreigners as of 16 March, only those who had been granted residence in the country or visas exceeding 90 days, and Czech citizens would be prohibited from leaving the country.
图7图8目前，意大利正处于疫情的暴发高峰期，政府出台了一系列新法，规定疑似病例患者若违反隔离规定，擅自外出并致严重后果，将以涉嫌故意谋杀罪论处，最高入刑逾20年。
Fig. 7 Fig. 8 Italy is currently at the peak of the epidemic, with a series of new laws that provide for the possibility of a suspected case of wilful murder with severe consequences if the patient goes out in violation of the quarantine regulations, with a maximum penalty of more than 20 years.
同时，米兰的方舱医院正在紧急搭建中，会展区旁将设500张重症监护床位。
Meanwhile, Milan's cabin hospital is under emergency construction, with 500 intensive care beds next to the convention area.
五、韩国超过26万人已接受检测图9截至3月14日0时，韩国境内共有261335人接受了病毒检测，其中235615人的检测结果呈阴性，还有17634人的检测结果尚未出炉。
Chart 9 More than 260,000 people in South Korea have been tested for the virus. As of 0000 hours March 14, a total of 261,335 people in South Korea had been tested, of whom 235,615 tested negative and 17,634 have yet to be tested.
有消息称，韩国政府将于15日宣布大邱和庆尚北道为特别灾区，将成韩国首次因传染病指定特别灾区。
South Korea's government will declare Daegu and Gyeongshan North Province as special disaster areas on the 15th, it said. It will be the first time South Korea has designated a special disaster area for infectious diseases.
政府将在被宣布特别灾区的地方展开调查，规划重建，国库支援50%的重建费用；同时，也将支援该地区的防疫管理、稳定民生、死伤者抚恤等费用，并享受电费、健康保险费、电话费和燃气费等减免优惠。
The government will carry out surveys and plans for reconstruction in areas declared particularly disaster-stricken areas. The State treasury will support 50 percent of the cost of reconstruction. It will also support epidemic prevention management, livelihood stability, compensation for the dead and injured, and enjoy preferential treatment in electricity, health insurance, telephone and gas charges.
图103月3日，韩国总统文在寅称，韩国军医学研究所研发的快速检测法，能将新冠病毒的检测时间从6个小时缩短到20分钟。
South Korean President Wen Jiabao said Wednesday that a rapid test developed by the South Korean Institute of Military Medicine could reduce detection time for the new crown virus from six hours to 20 minutes.
至3月9日，基本上完成了对新天地教会21万教众的检测。
By 9 March, the testing of 210,000 members of the Church of Xintiandi had been substantially completed.
虽然仍需警惕一些零星偶发的感染事件，但韩国的经验依旧表明，大力检测和追踪接触者，加上社交距离措施和社区动员，可以预防感染和拯救生命。
While some sporadic cases of infection still need to be guarded against, the Korean experience continues to show that aggressive testing and tracing of contacts, together with social distance measures and community mobilization, can prevent infection and save lives.
六、伊朗要求全民居家隔离图11伊朗武装力量总参谋长巴盖里3月13日下午宣布，为防控新冠肺炎疫情，全国将在24小时内清空公共场所不必要的人群，疏散所有街道和购物中心的居民。
Iran's chief of staff, Sergei Bagheri, announced on the afternoon of March 13 that in order to prevent and control the outbreak of pneumonia, the country will clear public places and evacuate all street and shopping center residents within 24 hours.
军方要求所有居民留在家中。
The military asked all residents to stay at home.
伊朗还计划增加约1000家固定和移动诊所，以帮助遏制疫情。
Iran also plans to add about 1,000 fixed and mobile clinics to help contain the outbreak.
伊朗外长扎里夫在12日表示，伊朗已向国际货币基金组织（IMF）申请50亿美元紧急贷款，以抗击新冠肺炎疫情对于伊朗经济的重大冲击。
Iran has applied for a $5 billion emergency loan from the International Monetary Fund to combat the devastating impact of the outbreak of pneumonia in Iran, Iranian Foreign Minister Hoshyar Zarif said Wednesday.
海南医学院第二附属医院(下称“海医二院”)14日向伊朗驻广州总领事馆捐赠防护服500套、自制简易面屏1500套，支持伊朗抗击新冠肺炎疫情。
Hainan Second Affiliated Hospital (Hainan Medical College) donated 500 suits of protective clothing and 1,500 self-made disposable screens to the Iranian Consulate General in Guangzhou to support Iran's fight against the New Crown Pneumonia epidemic.
【特别说明：以上统计，2月28日前为世卫组织官方统计数据，数据截止时间为北京时间每日17时；从2月28日开始，数据由《财经》根据公开资料统计，截止时间为北京时间每日9时】七、全球疫情数字速览：1、【复岗率80%】工业和信息化部负责人3月13日表示，目前，除湖北以外，全国规模以上工业企业平均开工率超过95%，企业人员平均复岗率约为80%；中小企业开工率已达到60%左右。
With the exception of Hubei province, the average start-up rate of industrial enterprises above the national scale exceeds 95 percent, and the average reemployment rate of workers in enterprises is about 80 percent, with the exception of Hubei Province, where the start-up rate of small and medium-sized enterprises has reached 60 percent.
此外，银保监会表示，银行业金融机构为抗击疫情提供的信贷支持已超过1.4万亿元，并要求对受疫情影响，暂时遇到困难的中小微企业不得抽贷、压贷、断贷，积极支持保险机构帮助企业渡过难关。
In addition, the CBRC said that the credit support provided by banking financial institutions to combat the epidemic had exceeded 1.4 trillion yuan, and required that MSMEs affected by the epidemic and experiencing temporary difficulties not be allowed to draw loans, suppress loans or suspend loans, and actively support insurance institutions to help enterprises tide over the difficulties.
2、【让6成居民感染】英国政府首席科学家瓦伦斯（Sir Patrick Vallance）建议让英国60%的人逐渐感染，患上轻症。
Let Six Adults Get Infected Sir Patrick Vallance, the British government's chief scientist, has suggested that 60 per cent of the UK population should develop mild cases of the disease.
这样，大家一起产生对这个病毒开始有免疫力。
In this way, people together began to have immunity to the virus.
从而从整个国家来说，这将帮助到全国的人。
And for the country as a whole, it will help people across the country.
因为从历史上所有的流行病来看，就算短期被抑制了。
Because of all the epidemics in history, even if the short-term is suppressed.
而当隔离措施取消之后，疫情又会卷土重来。
And when the quarantine is lifted, the epidemic will return.
英国现在的措施就是为了防止疫情在今年冬天重新到来，爆发更大的高峰。
What the UK is doing now is trying to prevent the outbreak from restarting this winter, with even bigger peaks.
小结：国内27省市区实现零新增，7省区和澳门现有病例清零。
Summary: 27 provinces and municipalities in the country to achieve zero new cases, 7 provinces and Macao existing cases are zero.
期待更多的零新增，期待更多的病例数归零。
Expect more zero new cases and zero more cases expected.
欧洲已成为全球疫情最严重的地区，多国采取封关措施以减缓疫情。
Europe has become the worst affected region in the world, with many countries adopting containment measures to mitigate the epidemic.
美国总统特朗普也将接受病毒检测。
US President Trump will also be tested for the virus.
